  "query": "What are the most effective ways to increase soil organic carbon on loamy soils?",
  "answer": "The most effective ways to increase soil organic carbon on loamy soils are to amend the soil with chemical compounds, adopt no-tillage or reduced tillage practices, and reduce grazing intensity.\n\nAmending the soil with formulated chemical compounds is a beneficial way to increase soil organic carbon, with five out of six studies showing an increase in soil organic matter or carbon when nitrogen or phosphorus fertilizer was applied (909). Another highly effective method is to change tillage practices. Twelve studies found that soils under no-tillage or reduced tillage systems had higher soil organic carbon compared to conventionally tilled soil (906). One review also showed that no-tillage with cover cropping and manure application increases soil organic carbon (906). Furthermore, reducing grazing intensity can also lead to increased soil carbon. One study found that excluding grazing animals led to an increase in both soil carbon and nitrogen (901). Another study showed that reducing grazing time in forage crops led to higher soil phosphate levels and less sediment erosion (901).",
